originalText.text: As soon as I got in my car after picking it up, I KNEW something was wrong. There were hand prints all over my windshield. I thought it was on the inside but it was the outside. I wiped it off, and then realized the same hand and fingerprints were all over my hood and the front part of my roof. So either someone was climbing on TOP OF MY CAR on their hands and knees, or Spider-Man frequents this garage at night. Either way, there’s absolutely no reason or excuse for this

originalText.text: Made a simple mistake and took my car keys by accident and didn't realize it till about an hour after. I went to take the keys as soon as i realized and the person in charge at 1:45 pm on Friday 3/17 was very rude and nasty saying that he didn't care and charging a very high and extra cost for the mistake. The attendant was very rude and disrespectful. It had been my first time ever there and i didn’t even notice the sign. I get it was a mistake and maybe i had to pay the price for it but he didn’t need to be so nasty and ride to a customer.

originalText.text: Was booked for a parking spot here on June 21st at 10pm. When I arrived, they were overbooked. Instead of being helpful, the attendant locked me out, swore at me, and spat out of the locked gate towards my car. Nice hiring, whoever runs this place

originalText.text: BEWARE: if your plans change and you need to get your car earlier than the time you told them, they will make it extremely difficult for you and will threaten to keep your car for 2 hours until they're "not busy".  When you protest and demand they retrieve your car, for which you're paying them, they get up in your face and you may fear that they will become violent (they didn't but it was that uncomfortable).  They told me not to park here again.  Well, I'm sorry but life happens and plans change, I needed my car.  What if it was a true emergency?  I have parked here several weekends a month for 4 years and have not had a problem until I had to get the car earlier than I communicated.
